{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17508368","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17508368"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:04:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:04:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2748"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2748","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2748"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.3,0.62,0,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2748"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78823"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2748","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2748"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2748"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64172"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3033"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3603"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3636"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7345"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27019"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38440"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39849"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42562"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43206"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78823","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78823"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 86-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with vague, generalised abdominal pain. This pain has been present for several months and is not getting better, but it does get worse at times and does not radiate. She denies vomiting, bowel changes, or urine changes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, her vital signs are normal and her abdomen is soft. A recent set of investigations have been completed and were unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer case records show she has presented nearly every month for the past year for either similar abdominal pain or chest pain, with no diagnosis being given after full investigation. Her husband of 50 years died three years ago and she has no family support in Australia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient says she is very sad and does not want to live. She has a poor appetite and has stopped eating. She has no energy and finds it very hard to sleep, which has got worse recently and she struggles to care for herself as she has no motivation. Her sisters both live in Greece and she has been unable to travel there for two years due to travel restrictions. She has a medical history of hypertension and bipolar affective disorder.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alzheimer\u2019s dementia","Major depressive episode","Major depressive disorder","Delirium","Adjustment disorder"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is an unfortunately common scenario in elderly patients and the delineation between depression, dementia and delirium can be difficult. The patient describes somatic symptoms likely secondary to their psychiatric state as well as many symptoms of \u003Cstrong\u003Edepression\u003C/strong\u003E including poor sleep, decreased appetite, low energy, low mood and poor self care. These have been escalating over three years following the death of her husband and she has no supports in Australia. It is also relevant to consider patient\u2019s within their cultural context and the strong family as well as country ties Greek people have, making her current situation even more distressing for her. This patient is experiencing a \u003Cstrong\u003EMajor Depressive Episode\u003C/strong\u003E as part of her underlying Bipolar Disorder. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf she did not have a history of Bipolar Disorder (ie a history of mania) then the diagnosis would be Major Depressive Disorder. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is unlikely to be \u003Cstrong\u003Eadjustment disorder\u003C/strong\u003E as it is prolonged over 3 years. It is also unlikely to be \u003Cstrong\u003Edelirium\u003C/strong\u003E as it sounds progressive rather than fluctuating and there is no obvious cause of delirium on history. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDementia\u003C/strong\u003E can present in the fashion above in terms of a prolonged, insidious decline in functioning and further behaviour psychotic symptoms of dementia (BPSD) can encompass this. However, there is a focus in the history of her inability to care for herself being secondary to neurovegetative symptoms of depression as well as there being a clear onset. Further, there is a lack of typical BPSD symptoms including wandering, agitation, and word finding difficulty.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Careful history is needed to delineate depression and dementia in the elderly.","Major depressive episodes can present with somatic symptoms, especially in older adults.","Social isolation and recent bereavement are significant risk factors for depression in the elderly."],"references":["Victoria Health. Differential diagnosis - depression, delirium and dementia. Victorian State Government. 2017. Available from: https://www2.health.vic.gov.au/hospitals-and-health-services/patient-care/older-people/cognition/diff-diagnosis.","Small GW. Differential diagnoses and assessment of depression in elderly patients. J Clin Psychiatry. 2009 Dec;70(12):e47. doi: 10.4088/JCP.8001tx20c. PMID: 20141704. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20141704/","Sekhon S, Patel J, Sapra A. Late-Life Depression. [Updated 2023 Jun 26]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK551507/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64172"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2748"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64172","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64172"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-12T20:05:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-12T20:06:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2748"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78823"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"r